File: Pieter Doorewaard (L) and Phillip Schutte(R) were sentenced to 18 and 23 years in prison respectively for the murder of Matlhomola Moshoeu. JOHANNESBURG - Two men convicted of killing a teenager in Coligny are petitioning the Supreme Court of Appeal to overturn their convictions. Advocate Barry Roux will take the matter to the SCA on behalf of Pieter Doorewaard and Phillip Schutte. READ: AfriForum to oppose Coligny murder case sentencing The pair were sentenced to 18 and 23-years in prison respectively, for the murder of Matlhomola Moshoeu. AfriForum is financing the appeal application. READ: Sunflower murder: Father unhappy with sentence It follows the admission by various people that the sole eyewitness in the case, Bonakele Pakisi, lied in court. AfriForum says it's confident the convictions will be set aside.